DocumentChange.text:
Complete as many of the tasks as you can in the hour and a half time limit. There is no specific order in
which you must complete tasks. When you are finished, please let us know.
Tasks:
Using the Swing/AWT Toolkit and any Java programming resources:
- Create a program that visually represents a car with a red body and two black tires.
- Allow the user to use arrow keys to move around the car in any direction (up, forward, left, and
right) by 10 pixel decrements/increments.
- Allow the user to make the car a bus by clicking anywhere on the screen
o A bus has an extra body that should be colored black. It should be positioned directly on
top of the car.
o When the extra body is on top of the car, it should move with the rest of it.
o The extra body should be removed
- Allow the user to make the bus a car by pressing the ‘r’ key
- Allow the user to scale up the car/bus 2X, each time they press the ‘m’ key
- Allow the user to scale down the car/bus 2X, each time they press the ‘s’ key
- Draw a transparent square (not a rectangle) with yellow borders. The car/bus should be inside
the square.
- Do not allow the car/bus to go outside of the square (when moving and resizing the vehicle).
o The extra body should be removed
o The extra body should be removed

Command.snapshot:
Complete as many of the tasks as you can in the hour and a half time limit. There is no specific order in which you must complete tasks. When you are finished, please let us know.
Using the Swing/AWT Toolkit and any Java programming resources:
- Create a program that visually represents a car with a red body and two black tires.
- Allow the user to use arrow keys to move the car around in any direction (up, forward, left, and right) by 10 pixel decrements/increments.
- Allow the user to make the car a two-story bus by clicking anywhere on the screen o A two-story bus has an extra body that should be colored black. It should be positioned directly on top of the car. o When the extra body is on top of the car, it should move with the rest of it.
- Allow the user to make the two-story bus a car by pressing the ‘r’ key o The extra body should be removed
- Allow the user to scale up the car/two-story bus 2X, each time they press the ‘m’ key - Allow the user to scale down the car/two-story bus 2X, each time they press the ‘s’ key
- Draw a transparent square (not a rectangle) with yellow borders. The car/two-story bus should be inside the square. - Do not allow the car/two-story bus to go outside of the square (when moving and resizing the vehicle).
